# Zoe Project Context

Zoe production code lives in `/home/zoe/assistant`. The live web/chat API is `services/zoe-data/` running host uvicorn on port 8000. `services/zoe-core/` is the wired default `core` brain fallback (Pi on Gemma 4, `pi --mode rpc`) below the live `flue` sidecar — extend it, do not retire it. The truly-retired thing is the OLD Docker/RouteLLM-MemAgent monolith (git history only).

Repository changes should land through pull requests. Keep `main` protected and treat direct pushes or admin merges as emergency-only operator-approved actions.

Use one production chat router: `services/zoe-data/routers/chat.py`. Natural-language routing belongs in `intent_router.py` or Zoe Agent (Hermes/OpenClaw are retirement targets — never destinations); do not add brittle command-detection branches to `chat.py`.

Before file changes, follow `.zoe/AI_ASSISTANT_CHECKLIST.md`: validate structure, respect `.zoe/manifest.json`, and keep root markdown at or below 10 files. Do not delete files without the cleanup safety process.

Zoe is multi-user and scope-aware. Memory writes must carry scope, credentials are per user/scope, and core code must not bake in home/family/household assumptions.

Hermes is being retired behind the Flue executor migration (docs/architecture/multica-executor-migration.md). OpenClaw is being FULLY RETIRED (operator decision 2026-07-22) — route nothing to it; its runtime and builder intents are slated for deletion via gated PRs. Rebuild needed capabilities on Pi/Flue.
